The paper presents a new method for pupil detection in video-based eye tracking, which is a common technique used in various research fields such as computer vision (cs.CV), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), multimedia (cs.MM), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also compares the proposed method with other open-source algorithms, which further supports the relevance of the paper to these sub-categories.
